26/02/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- NATO Deputy Secretary General Alessandro Minuto Rizzo told Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic on Friday (24 February) that Croatia has achieved solid progress in implementing reforms needed for NATO membership. 
During his visit to Zagreb, Rizzo reiterated that he cannot say whether Croatia would be formally invited to join the Alliance this year, but noted the country is now much closer to entry. 
Grabar-Kitarovic announced that a public information campaign stressing the advantages of NATO membership would be launched soon. 
(Novi list - 25/02/06; HINA, HRT - 24/02/06)
